title: I. Array sorting
statement: Sorting arrays is traditionally associated with high-level languages. How hard can it be in Befunge? Sort the given array in non-descending order.
inputSpecification: The first line of input contains an integer n (1 ≤ n ≤ 100) — the size of the array. The following n lines contain the elements of the array, one per line. Each element of the array is an integer between 1 and 60, inclusive. The array might contain duplicate elements.
outputSpecification: Output space-separated elements of the sorted array.
name: Array sorting
